Package Main

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Renderer
    Public interface Renderer is used to create an interface for renderers to be created.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Ball
    Public class Ball is used to create a ball for the game with the given center point and diameter.
    BallTest
    BallTest tests to see if the methods of Ball class which are all setters and getters are all working properly.
    Brick
    Public class Brick is used to create bricks for the game with the given brickId, point and dimensions.
    BrickBreaker
    Public class BrickBreaker is responsible for loading in the GameEngine to start generating the game.
    BrickTest
    BrickTest tests to see if the methods of Brick class which are all setters and getters are all working properly.
    CustomConsole
    Public class CustomConsole is the container for the CustomPanel.
    CustomPanel
    Public class CustomPanel is used customise the levels based on the player choice such as level type, number of balls, number of rows of bricks, number of bricks in a row, number of brick types and brick types that spawn.
    DebugConsole
    Public class DebugConsole is the container for the DebugPanel.
    DebugPanel
    Public class DebugPanel is used to call methods to reset ball count, reset ball and player position, move to previous or next level and set the ball movement speed.
    GameBoard
    Public class GameBoard is the Model of the MVC design pattern and is responsible for holding all the entity information of the game such as bricks, ball and player.
    GameBoardController
    Public class GameBoardController is the Controller of the MVC design pattern and is responsible for processing all the entity behaviour in the game.
    GameBoardControllerTest
    GameBoardControllerTest tests to see if the methods of GameBoardController class are all working properly.
    GameBoardRenderer
    Public class GameBoardRenderer is the View of the MVC design pattern and is responsible for rendering all the graphics in the game.
    GameBoardTest
    GameBoardTest tests to see if the methods of GameBoard class which are all setters and getters are all working properly.
    GameEngine
    Public class GameBoard is responsible for loading in the GameBoard, Controller and Renderer.
    GameFrame
    Public class GameFrame is responsible for loading between all the different screens in the game.
    GameSounds
    Public class GameSounds is responsible for adding audio to the game such as BGM and sound effects.
    GodModePowerUp
    Public class GodModePowerUp is used to create a power up for the game with the given center point and diameter.
    GodModePowerUpTest
    GodModePowerUpTest tests to see if the methods of GodModePowerUp class which are all setters and getters are all working properly.
    GraphicsMain
    Public class GraphicsMain is used to load the GameFrame which will load all the different screens of the game and then show the HomeMenu.
    Highscore
    Public class Highscore is responsible for generating and showing the top 10 highest scores for each level and the total highscore for the game on the Highscore Board which can be reached from the HomeMenu.
    HomeMenu
    Public class HomeMenu is the first screen the player sees when starting the game.
    InfoScreen
    Public class InfoScreen is used to display information about the game and explains all the different functionalities of the game so that the player may better enjoy the game.
    Player
    Public class Player creates a rectangle shape with which the player controls to bounce the ball towards the bricks.
    PlayerTest
    PlayerTest tests to see if the methods of Player class which are all setters and getters are all working properly.
    Score
    Class Score is used as a linked list to load and hold the basic information about the player such as ranking, name, level type, time and score after completing a level.
    ScoreBoard
    Public class ScoreBoard is responsible for showing the list of highscores for that level at the end of every level and also the highscores for the whole game at the end of the game.
    ScoreComp
    Class ScoreComp is a comparator to compare the scores and time of all the players to generate a ranking list.
